text:
Aqu√≠ asumimos:
\[Y_i \mid \boldsymbol\beta,\sigma \sim \mathcal{N}(\boldsymbol\beta^T \mathbf{x}_i, \sigma^2)\]
o bien decimos
\[
\begin{align*}
    Y_i & \sim  \mathcal{N}(\mu_i, \sigma^2) \\
    \mu_i & = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_{1_i} + \beta_2 x_{2_i} + \dots + \beta_p x_{p_i}
\end{align*}
\]
Y completamos el modelo especificando una distribuci√≥n a priori \(p(\boldsymbol\beta,\sigma)\)

posterior &lt;- inner_join(prior, likelihood) |&gt;
  mutate(posterior = prior * likelihood)

